@startuml
' Verification is structural: the Critic-gated loop's ONLY path to End runs through the
' Critic's `pass` branch, so the machine cannot terminate with an unverified result.
' Palette: work=indigo, critic=gold, pass/end=green, fail/loop=red.
skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam defaultFontName Inter
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #e0e7ff
  BorderColor #3730a3
  FontColor #1e1b4b
}

state "μL (loop head)" as L
state "O→S:attempt_req" as Req
state "S→O:attempt" as Att
state "O→C:verify_req" as Ver
state CriticGate <<choice>> #fef9c3
state "O→S:release · end" as Done #dcfce7

[*] --> L
L --> Req
Req --> Att
Att --> Ver
Ver --> CriticGate : C→O : verdict
CriticGate --> Done : **pass**  (the ONLY exit)
CriticGate --> L : **fail**  (back-edge — try again)
Done --> [*]

note right of CriticGate #fef9c3
  the Critic owns the gating Choice;
  workers are bystanders → projection
  MERGES both branches (same-sender Recv)
end note
note bottom of Done #dcfce7
  the machine cannot reach End without a `pass`
  ⇒ no termination with an unverified result
end note
@enduml
